We have an opportunity for a  Project Controls Specialist  for our Project Controls Group in Newton, MA. As a Project Controls Specialist, you will be a member of our Nationwide Project Controls Group supporting some of the most exciting and icon projects and programs. Our Project Controls Group provides services in the areas of Cost Engineering, Scheduling, Estimating, Document Control, Risk Management. In addition, our team also encompasses a Project Technology Group which delivers value to our clients through leveraging leading-edge technologies throughout the project and program lifecycles and drives value to our end clients through the use of machine learning and artificial intelligence. 
The Project Controls Specialist will be responsible for management and performance of a team in all estimating, scheduling and project controls functions for building construction, healthcare, transportation and infrastructure projects including change order analysis and negotiation; constructability reviews of project plans and specifications (both in progress and completed designs), risk management and value engineering. The Project Controls Specialist will ensure the effective review of construction design drawings & specifications, supervises office and/or field teams to ensure the team gathers all material and data necessary to organize the required activities and produce final documentation for review by management before issuance to the client. 
Responsible for the identification and evaluation of potential opportunities, presenting data and developing the summary effect of initiatives to STV management an clients as required. Will have a demonstrated ability to manage a team of staff, of various disciplines, to accurately and efficiently complete deliverables and meet deadlines. Will report monthly on progress to the project controls director and project executive. Will identify potential opportunities for the expansion of the STV team and engage with the client to secure additional positions when available. 
The Project Controls Specialist will need to able to work in STV offices and project sites in the Boston, MA metropolitan area. Occasional or in-frequent travel may be required to other cities. 
Required Skills: 
Must have a minimum of 5 years of experience with the project cost management and earned value performance measurement. 
The ideal candidate must have a Bachelorâ€™s degree in Construction Management, Business, Architecture, Engineering or a related field from an accredited College or University. 
Experience with Healthcare projects is preferred but not required. 
Experience with Microsoft Office Suite, PMWeb, BIM, and Primavera P6 is desired. 
